Global Investment House KSCC, a
Kuwaiti investment bank that reorganized $1.73 billion of debt
in 2009, said it will meet bondholders on April 24 as part of
the restructuring process.  There will be separate meetings in  Kuwait City  with holders
of its 50 million-dinar ($180 million) bond and of its 45
million-dinar bond, the bank said in a statement distributed on
the Regulatory News Service.  To contact the reporter on this story:
